LAGOS – Fast-rising Afrobeats and Afrofusion singer, Popoola Mubarak Ayomide, fondly addressed as King Mubaraq, has reminisced on his career and life and his forthcoming project. King Mubaraq, having released his much anticipated Extended Play titled ‘Past Tense’, which consisted of melodious songs like ‘Bite Me’ Laga Dat’, and ‘Change’, among others, said the project has greatly contributed to his life. “The turnout and love shown by my fans on the project really gave my career a fast progression and for that, I’m grateful to my fans all over. Because I knew where I was before the project was released and now that it’s everywhere.” He, however, spoke about his upcoming single, noting that it will be released soon. “I have been in the studio working around the clock to do something bigger this time. I will be dropping a follow-up on the single very soon.”